 :tx/rationale "ONLINE vs BOOTSTRAP vs BATCH CALIBRATION tradeoff analysis: (1) BOOTSTRAP AT INIT (proposed earlier): Computes threshold from innate-to-innate similarities. Problem: synthetic data, not representative of real observation-to-concept distribution. (2) BATCH AT HARVEST (current): Correct but too late — all observations use stale bootstrap default. (3) ONLINE PER-OBSERVATION (proposed now): Updates threshold after each observation using running sufficient statistics. Converges in 3-5 observations. No synthetic data. No stale-until-harvest gap. Cost: 3 extra datoms written per observation (negligible vs the 9+ already written). The online approach subsumes both bootstrap and batch — it IS the bootstrap (observations 1-5) AND the ongoing calibration (observations 6+). The harvest Otsu becomes a periodic full-recalculation audit. Traces to: ADR-FOUNDATION-031, C9."
